The provisions of this Part shall not have effect where possession of an infant has been, is, or is proposed to be taken—
(a) by any person for a purely temporary purpose;
by any person for a purely temporary purpose;
(b) by a school, hospital, convalescent home or other similar institution;
by a school, hospital, convalescent home or other similar institution;
(c) by an institution to which the infant has been committed under the provisions of the Mental Disorders Act; or
by an institution to which the infant has been committed under the provisions of the Mental Disorders Act; or
(d) by any reformatory, approved school, house or home approved under the provisions of the Juveniles Act for the reception of juveniles.
