(1) It shall not be lawful for an adopter, or for a parent or guardian of an infant , to receive, except with the sanction of the court , any payment or other reward in consideration of the adoption of an infant under the provisions of this Act, or for any person to make or give or agree to make or give to an adopter, parent or guardian any payment or reward, the receipt of which is prohibited by this subsection.
